stylometry:
A sensitivity analysis is altering one cell in a formila and seeing how the results of the problem change by doing so.  Doing a sensitivity analysis is important because in business planning, you want to leave some room for change or error because you cannot predict the future and how outside factors will affect your business plans. By doing a sensitivity analysis you can see how much room there is for error or change and how that affects the other components in your model.

Solver Table creates a table or graph for you showing all the solutions with different inputs, it allows you to see a variety of solutions for the same problem or model.
